Requirements from you (Ben) to unblock Firebase App Distribution:

Naomi cannot complete the setup autonomously due to authentication and environment constraints. Here's the precise list of what is needed:

Firebase Project & Access
Create (or provide access to) a real Firebase project in the Firebase Console.
Enable App Distribution in that project.
Create a tester group (or share the project with your account so Naomi can configure it).

Authentication (Critical Blocker)
Firebase CLI login is browser-based and requires a GUI. Options:
Provide a Firebase service account JSON key (recommended for CI/headless use), or
Perform firebase login yourself on a machine with a browser and share the resulting token/refresh credentials.

SDK / Toolchain Installation
On a development machine (or GitHub Actions runner) with GUI:
Install Flutter SDK + Android SDK + platform tools + accept licenses.
Set ANDROID_HOME, JAVA_HOME, and update PATH.
Run flutter doctor and resolve all issues.

Project Configuration
Update pubspec.yaml with actual Firebase dependencies.
Replace placeholder values in firebase.json and add real google-services.json / GoogleService-Info.plist.
Configure the app in Firebase Console (Android + iOS packages).

Distribution Flow
Once the above is done, Naomi can:
Build a signed APK.
Upload via firebase appdistribution:distribute.
Generate the tester link.

Preferred path (to match your no-USB preference):
Provide a Firebase service account + project access → Naomi sets up a GitHub Actions workflow that handles builds + distribution automatically.

Reply with which items you can handle or provide (e.g., service account key, project ID), and Naomi will execute the rest.
